;       *** Lower Eltinmar Farmland/Ferry
;
NUMBER 524
NAME Grassland, Small Rise
PLAIN
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
This rise marks the southern end of the lowlands. To the south, down a rocky
trail, lay the shores of the Inner Sea. The breeze gently ruffles the grass and
sparse shrubs resting at the top of this rise and harbors the rank and bitter
smell of the sea. Far to the north one can faintly see the chimneys and
rooftops of Fayd.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 1119
EXIT N 522
ITEM 0 82 ADJ1=264 VAL2=525
;
NUMBER 1100
NAME Coastal trail
PLAIN
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
This worn wagon track leads off through the low grasslands of the coastal
area around the Inner Sea. A low, gradual slope leads down from the banks of
the Eltinmar to the east, and heads more or less straight west, veering away
from the ocean and toward a copse of small trees.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 1101
EXIT E 1117
;
NUMBER 1101
NAME Coastal trail, Copse
PLAIN
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
The worn dirt of the wagon trail bisects a small copse of scraggly trees,
which have been bent and twisted by the wind coming off the sea. Other than
the trees, there is not much plantlife around besides the pervasive grass
that seems to be hardy enough to survive in the barren soil. The track leads
from east to southwest here.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 1100
EXIT SW 1102
;
NUMBER 1102
NAME Coastal trail
*DESCRIPTION_START
A low range of sandy hills separates the trail from sight of the sea here.
The sound of the ocean still reaches you faintly from beyond the barrier,
and the smell of salt air is yet strong, but the trail curves here to the
southwest, away from the shoreline and up and over another small rise.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 1101
EXIT SW 1103
;
NUMBER 1103
NAME Coastal trail, atop a rise
PLAIN
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
The trail reaches the top of a small hill here, and heads down to the west
into a long low valley. From your vantage, you can see that the valley is not
as rich as those east of Fayd, but a few small farming communities seemed to
have used irrigation to their benefit.  At the peak of the hill, a ring of
odd trees groups a large number of demons who are amusing themselves with
a young girl from one of the farms.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 1102
EXIT W 1104
;
NUMBER 1104
NAME Wagon Track
PLAIN
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
You pass among the coastal farmland. Fields and farmhouses dot the countryside
in a patchwork pattern of differnet colored crops. The trail heads east back
toward the coast of the Inner Sea, and southwest toward a range of hills. A
narrower wagon track, its grooves worn deep into the earth, meanders north up
a small rise. All along the road, demons swarm and mill about causing mayhem
and havoc.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 1103
EXIT SW 1105
ITEM 0 609 ADJ1=439 VAL2=1120
;
NUMBER 1105
NAME Base of Valley
PLAIN
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
The wagon track heads up into a wide mountain valley here to your west. The
mountains are low and eroded, but are covered by a growth of forest. Some
of the demons spill down into the valley.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 1104
EXIT W 1106
