NUMBER 1106
NAME Wagon Track
PLAIN
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
The track heads farther up the valley. But a pair of stone buildings catch
your eye. To the southwest, on a low hill, you can see the mangled profile of a
what used to be a small keep. To the north, on an opposing hillock is the black
form of a towering fortress, seemingly decrepit and abandoned. The way to the
north is blocked by a deep chasm.
*DESCRIPTION_END
