NUMBER 1117
NAME Lower Eltinmar, Western Dock
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
From your vantage on the short ferry dock, you can see the expanse of the
lower Eltinmar. The river is broad and slow here where its murky depths flow
into the Inner Sea. Heavily laden cargo ships of all shapes and size make
their way up and down the navigable part of the river between the sea and the
docks of Fayd. A well-travelled wagon track leads up and away from the dock
over a low rise to the west.
*DESCRIPTION_END
