Number 1120
Name Manor, Grounds
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
*DESCRIPTION_START
   In the distance, on level but swampy ground, slumps a dark manor. It
must be constructed of stone, you think, but it appears to be covered
over in a thick layer of...mud? slime? You hesitate to know the true
answer. A tall black fence of goodly height surrounds the building and a
small bit of ground around it. There is something odd about the
appearance of the fence...something perched awkwardly on top of the
posts...but at this distance you can't be sure what it is.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 609 ADJ1=439 VAL2=1104
EXIT NW 1113
EXIT NE 1121
;
Number 1121
Name Manor, Gate
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
   This close, the manor looms over you like a hulking, bad-tempered
giant, oozing slime and trailing vines as though it sprang up from the
ground around it. The tall fence barring your path inside is made of
heavy wrought iron, its vertical bars spaced every two feet, its
horizontals at one foot, four feet, and seven feet from the ground.
Following the line of the posts upwards, you discover what is perched
atop the sharpened vertical bars. The severed heads of the farm families,
in various stages of decay, leer crookedly down at you. The gate before
you sports the iron face of a creature out of nightmare, so ugly you
can't keep your eyes on it for more than a few seconds at a time.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT SW 1120
ITEM 0 <gate> VAL1=180 VAL2=1122 VAL3=1122 VAL4=9001
