Number 1123
Name Manor, Hallway
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
   A fetid stench assails your senses as you walk into this hallway, so
strong it nearly makes your eyes water. It seems to be composed of
rotting vegetation, marsh gas, and another semi-familiar odor that makes
your instincts cry a warning. The hallway is dim and dank, extending
beyond your sight into murky shadow. A rotting, faded rug beneath your
feet muffles your footsteps. There are paintings on the dark walls, but
they are so covered in dust and cobwebs you cannot make out their
subjects. Several rooms lead off this hallway through arched doors of
heavy dark wood.
*DESCRIPTION_END
