   This long, high-ceilinged room is panelled in dark wood, with candle
sconces every few feet along the walls and a large dusty chandelier in
the middle of the ceiling. A positively huge table, of heavy ebony wood,
dominates the center of the room. It looks as though it could seat at
least fifty people at once. Chairs upholstered in faded red velvet
surround the table, and more are pushed back against the walls.
