;
Number 1126
Name Manor, Bedroom
INDOOR_FLOOR
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
   You feel your jaw drop in awe when you walk into this room; the size
of the bed is beyond anything you have seen or imagined. It looks like
it could easily hold fifty people; the fifty people that dined at the
massive table in the dining room. The high bedstead is carved of dark maple in
what at first appear to be odd, sinuous curves, but on closer
examination are revealed to be suggestions for the occupants of the bed.
The dusty coverlet is faded and torn, once a rich indigo color, as are
the bed curtains hanging between the bedposts. A thick dusty rug
silences your feet, and heavy curtains drawn across a great bow window
darken the room into near night. A large heavy wardrobe stands against
one wall.
*DESCRIPTION_END
