Number 1127
Name Manor, Kitchen
INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
   A massive fireplace takes up one whole wall in this room, the stones
of its construction darkened by years of soot and dust. A large pile of
ashes all but buries the roasting spit in the center of the fireplace. A
pothook extends out over the ashes, an old kettle hanging from it. A
large table and several smaller ones are scattered about the room, their
surfaces knife-scarred and stained. Several battered copper pans and
pots hang from hooks on the walls, but most are empty. The faint odor of
rotting food here makes you nauseous.
*DESCRIPTION_END
