INUMBER 1186
NAME 384
WEIGHT 1
VARIABLE JANUSBOOK
VARIABLE JANRECALLSET
IFPREVERB TURN -1
        CLEARVERB
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 8
                ECHO PLAYER You carefully close the book.
                ECHO OTHERS %N carefully close the leather cover of the book.
                EQUAL JANUSBOOK 0
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 7
                ECHO PLAYER You turn the parchment page of the book.
                ECHO OTHERS %N turns the parchment page of the book.
                EQUAL JANUSBOOK 8
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 6
                ECHO PLAYER You turn the parchment page of the book.
                ECHO OTHERS %N turns the parchment page of the book.
                EQUAL JANUSBOOK 7
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 5
                ECHO PLAYER You turn the parchment page of the book.
                ECHO OTHERS %N turns the parchment page of the book.
                EQUAL JANUSBOOK 6
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 4
                ECHO PLAYER You turn the parchment page of the book.
                ECHO OTHERS %N turns the parchment page of the book.
                EQUAL JANUSBOOK 5
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 3
                ECHO PLAYER You turn the parchment page of the book.
                ECHO OTHERS %N turns the parchment page of the book.
                EQUAL JANUSBOOK 4
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 2
                ECHO PLAYER You turn the parchment page of the book.
                ECHO OTHERS %N turns the parchment page of the book.
                EQUAL JANUSBOOK 3
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 1
                ECHO PLAYER You turn the parchment page of the book.
                ECHO OTHERS %N turns the parchment page of the book.
                EQUAL JANUSBOOK 2
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 0
                ECHO PLAYER You carefully open the book's leather cover.
                ECHO OTHERS %N carefully opens the book's leather cover.
                EQUAL JANUSBOOK 1
        ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB OPEN -1
        CLEARVERB
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK > 0
                ECHO PLAYER The book is already opened.
        ELSE
                ECHO PLAYER You carefully open the book's leather cover.
                ECHO OTHERS %N carefully opens the book's leather cover.
                EQUAL JANUSBOOK 1
        ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CLOSE -1
        CLEARVERB
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK ! 0
                ECHO PLAYER You carefully close the book.
                ECHO OTHERS %N carefully close the leather cover of the book.
                EQUAL JANUSBOOK 0
        ELSE
                ECHO PLAYER The book is already closed.
        ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB READ -1
CLEARVERB
IFVAR SKILL32 > 2
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 8
                ECHO PLAYER You are unable to make any sense of this page.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 7
                ECHO PLAYER You are unable to make any sense of this page.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 6
                ECHO PLAYER This page is entitled "The Guardian"
                ECHO PLAYER ------------------------------------
                ECHO PLAYER Now you must cause the elemental to enter unto the disk.
                ECHO PLAYER Cause the creature to stand astride the disk, and as the eight mages chant the following incantation...
                ECHO PLAYER (A string of magical runes follows, penned in a golden, shimmering ink.)
                ECHO PLAYER Bombard the element with the fire of the heavens until it is consumed. Its essence will be transferred to the disk, completing the seal.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 5
                ECHO PLAYER This page is entitled "The Fire"
                ECHO PLAYER --------------------------------
                ECHO PLAYER To give the disk the ability to withstand assault and to slay any who would undo it without the proper ritual, gather the following components and place them in the urn.
                ECHO PLAYER (Three obscure alchemical runes follow line the page at this point.)
                ECHO PLAYER When they components have been gathered into the urn, plcae the urn upon the disk and, and the eight wizards will incant the following spell:
                ECHO PLAYER (A string of magical runes follows, penned in a golden, shimmering ink.)
                ECHO PLAYER The urn will be consumed in a blistering fire.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 4
                ECHO PlAYER This page is entitled "The Armor"
                ECHO PLAYER ---------------------------------
                ECHO PLAYER To strengthen the disk and its guard, gather the following materials and place them on the disk as the elemental stands by:
                ECHO PLAYER (Four obscure alchemical runes follow line the page at this point.)
                ECHO PLAYER When they components have been gathered upon the disk, the eight mages will utter this incantation:
                ECHO PLAYER (A string of magical runes follows, penned in a golden, shimmering ink.)
                ECHO PLAYER The energy of this spell will arc between the element and its charge, bathing them in protective glow.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 3
                ECHO PlAYER This page is entitled "The Watching"
                ECHO PLAYER ------------------------------------
                ECHO PLAYER In a brass urn, you must gather together the specimens that will imbue the elemental with the power to watch over its charge.
                ECHO PLAYER (Three obscure alchemical runes follow line the page at this point.)
                ECHO PLAYER When they components have been gathered into the urn, cause the elemental to bear the urn in its arms, and the eight wizards will incant the following spell:
                ECHO PLAYER (A string of magical runes follows, penned in a golden, shimmering ink.)
                ECHO PLAYER The contents of the urn will be consumed, and the magic will enter into the element.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 2
                ECHO PLAYER This page is entitled "The Summoning"
                ECHO PLAYER -------------------------------------
                ECHO PLAYER To begin each seal, you must prepare a great disk of clay and an appropriate clay rune as its focus to hold the magic.
                ECHO PLAYER When this has been prepared, you must summon the greatest possible specimen of the appropriate elemental and cause it to approach the disk.
                ECHO PLAYER Then the ritual must begin.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 1
                ECHO PLAYER The most powerful of seals are those created with the elements. The four basic, and four more in their combinations, they will not fail their purpose when assaulted from within.
                ECHO PLAYER Even from without, once the seal is in place, it is extremely difficult and hazardous to undo. Only by a precise reversal of the original ritual can the stronger seals be broken.
                ECHO PLAYER Their strength however lies in there combined energy. Once one has been broken, the others will be weakened, and to be restored completely must be undone one and all.
                ECHO PLAYER Eight mages of no small strength are required, half of light, half of dark. All must be of the same intent for the ritual to succeed.
                ECHO PLAYER Guard this ritual well.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 0
                ECHO PLAYER The cover has been inlaid with gold leaf, but you can't make out the significance of the runes.
        ENDIF
ELSE
        ECHO PLAYER The script and runes in the book are beyond your learning.
ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB RECALL -1
IFVAR SKILL32 > 5
        CLEARVERB
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 8
                ECHO PLAYER You cannot make sense of anything on this page.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 7
                ECHO PLAYER You cannot make sense of anything on this page.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 6
                IFVAR SKILL32 > 10
                        IFVAR SKILL23 > 25
                                ECHO PLAYER The magical runes read:
                                ECHO PLAYER "Unto this home, this keep of clay."
                                ECHO PLAYER "We send you now, forever to stay..."
                                ECHO PLAYER "...the hands and feet of those who'd pass."
                                ECHO PLAYER "This magic shall forever last."
                        ENDIF
                ENDIF
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 5
                IFVAR SKILL31 > 2
                ECHO PLAYER The alchemical runes read:
                ECHO PLAYER Stinging tail, Fangs of armored lion, Smoking spit, tongue of stony gazing
                ENDIF
                IFVAR SKILL32 > 10
                        IFVAR SKILL23 > 25
                                ECHO PLAYER The magical runes read:
                                ECHO PLAYER "Fire we call to defend this seal."
                                ECHO PLAYER "Burn to ash, those who'd steal."
                        ENDIF
                ENDIF
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 4
                IFVAR SKILL31 > 2
                ECHO PLAYER The alchemical runes read:
                ECHO PLAYER Stone of servant, Stone man's chip, spine of basker, specimen of brain
                ENDIF
                IFVAR SKILL32 > 10
                        IFVAR SKILL23 > 25
                                ECHO PLAYER The magical runes read:
                                ECHO PLAYER "Gird about this disk of clay."
                                ECHO PLAYER "with armor to last the end of days."
                        ENDIF
                ENDIF
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 3
                IFVAR SKILL31 > 2
                ECHO PLAYER The alchemical runes read:
                ECHO PLAYER Eye most foul, Eye from deep, Eye of two-headed drakin
                ENDIF
                IFVAR SKILL32 > 10
                        IFVAR SKILL23 > 25
                                ECHO PLAYER The magical runes read:
                                ECHO PLAYER "Watcher watch eternal more."
                                ECHO PLAYER "See all who would approach this door."
                        ENDIF
                ENDIF
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 2
                ECHO PLAYER There is nothing further on this page to divine.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 1
                ECHO PLAYER There is nothing further on this page to divine.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR JANUSBOOK = 0
                ECHO PLAYER You can't make out the runes on the cover.
        ENDIF
ELSE
        ECHO PLAYER You are not learned enough to divine the runes.
ENDIF
ENDIF
